Step.Name: This scenario begin when the user brings up the available WiFi network list on your device.
WiFi Authentication
Upon accessing the WiFi ID from the list, the user should be redirected to a web page where they create/put in their credentials for authentication.
Credential Verification
Send an email/OTP to verify the credentials given.
Credential authentication
Verify the credentials to authenticate it as a success or failure based on the authentication protocols used.
Authentication Success
Verified credentials should be allowed to successfully access WiFi whenever in range.
Time limits can be set based on the type of accounts.
Authentication update can be automated to give seamless access to users across boards.
This scenario ends when the user is connected to the Internet
This scenario begins when the user fails authentication process for accessing WiFi.
Authentication Failure
Non-verified credentials should not be allowed to access WiFi.
Credential verification failure should automatically lead to no access.
Significant time gaps between auto-authentication update should lead to re-verification process.
Re-direction to the initial loading page
Redirect the user to initial loading page for re-verification of their credentials.
This scenario ends when the user has been redirected to go through the authentication process again.
